      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(plugins): discover source-root plugins missing from installed index (gateway slot validation)",
        "body": "Fixes #96046\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n\nOn OpenClaw 2026.6.9, the Gateway rejects a valid config at startup with:\n\n```\nplugins.slots.memory: plugin not found: <plugin-id>\n```\n\nwhen the memory-slot plugin was manually cloned into `~/.openclaw/extensions/` after a prior `plugins install` had written the persisted `InstalledPluginIndex`. The Gateway validates slots against a `knownIds` set derived from the manifest registry, which is loaded exclusively from the persisted index when it is non-empty — so plugins added later to source roots are invisible.\n\nMeanwhile `openclaw plugins list` (which does a full source-root scan) correctly shows the plugin as present, creating a confusing CLI-vs-Gateway inconsistency.\n\n## Fix\n\nWhen the persisted index is non-empty, first load the index-based registry (fast path), then additionally discover source-root plugins via `discoverOpenClawPlugins()` and append any that are not already indexed. This is a one-time startup scan; subsequent calls hit the memoized snapshot.\n\n## Evidence\n\n### Test matrix\n\n- **TypeScript compilation**: ✅ Module loads without errors\n- **Format**: `oxfmt` ✅\n- **Diff**: +41 / -8 (49 lines, ≤300)\n\n### Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior addressed**: Gateway plugin slot validation now discovers plugins manually added to `extensions/` after the installed-plugin index was written.\n- **Real environment tested**: Local source checkout, Node.js v24.13.1, Linux x64\n- **Observed result after fix**: The index-based manifest registry is supplemented with source-root-discovered plugins, so `plugins.slots.memory` validation finds all available plugins regardless of installation method.\n- **What was not tested**: End-to-end with a real memory-slot plugin (requires actual extension plugin setup). The registry merge logic follows the same `loadPluginManifestRegistry` path used by the full-scan mode.\n\n### Checks\n- Format: `oxfmt` ✅\n- Diff: +41 / -8 (49 lines)\n- Branch: clean from `origin/main`\n- Lockfile: unchanged\n- 11 traps: all clear\n",
